crumple /ˈkrʌmpəl/

(crumpling,crumpled,crumples) 

1. V-T/V-I If you crumple something such as paper or cloth, or if it crumples , it is squashed and becomes full of untidy creases and folds. 弄皱; 起皱 

例： She crumpled the paper in her hand. 她把手中的纸揉成了一团。 

2. PHRASAL VERB Crumple up means the same as . 弄皱 

例： She crumpled up her coffee cup. 她挤瘪了咖啡杯。 

3. crumpled ADJ 褶皱的 

例： His uniform was crumpled and untidy. 他的制服有很多褶皱, 而且不整洁。

